<p>I am trying to convert a traditional <strong>ASP.NET MVC</strong> postback view to use <strong>Angular</strong> and <strong>AJAX</strong> postbacks. My problem is that I am unable to determine the <strong>binding</strong> to get the proper values sent up to the server.</p>  <p>With the traditional form, the postback values looked like</p>  <pre><code>Request.SearchTerms = "error 123" Request.Facets.Index = 0 Request.Facets[0].Field = "priority" Request.Facets[0].Value = "low" Request.Facets.Index = 3 Request.Facets[3].Field = "priority" Request.Facets[3].Value = "medium" Request.Facets.Index = 8 Request.Facets[8].Field = "state" Request.Facets[8].Value = "open" </code></pre>  <p>This in turn gets bound (using MVC model binding) on the ASP.NET side to an object like</p>  <pre><code>public class Request {    public string SearchTerms { get; set; }    public IEnumerable&lt;Facet&gt; Facets { get; set; } }  public class Facet {    public string Field { get; set; }    public string Value { get; set; } } </code></pre>  <p>The <code>SearchTerms</code> binding is simple. Something like the following works.</p>  <pre><code>&lt;input type="text" ng-model="Request.SearchTerms" /&gt; </code></pre>  <p>My question is how to configure/bind using <strong>Angular</strong> and postback the <strong>Facets</strong> fields in the format specified at the beginning of the question.</p>